f3Pwe3MIB.name: f3Pwe3MIB
f3Pwe3MIB.contactinfo: Raghav Trivedi ADVA Optical Networking, Inc. Tel: +1 972 759-1239 E-mail: rtrivedi@advaoptical.com Postal: 2301 N. Greenville Ave. #300 Richardson, TX USA 75082
f3Pwe3MIB.description: This module provides the F3 Pseudo Wire definitions used by the F3 (FSP150CM/CC) product lines. Copyright (C) ADVA Optical Networking.

PWE3SatopDiscoveryType.name: PWE3SatopDiscoveryType
PWE3SatopDiscoveryType.description: Enumerations for PWE3 SATop Discovery Type.

PWE3SatopEncapsulationType.name: PWE3SatopEncapsulationType
PWE3SatopEncapsulationType.description: Enumerations for PWE3 SATop Encapsulation Type.

PWE3SatopRTPTSUpdateFreqType.name: PWE3SatopRTPTSUpdateFreqType
PWE3SatopRTPTSUpdateFreqType.description: Enumerations for PWE3 SATop RTP Update Frequency.

PWE3SatopTransportMode.name: PWE3SatopTransportMode
PWE3SatopTransportMode.description: Enumerations for PWE3 SATop Transport Mode.

MplsLabel.name: MplsLabel
MplsLabel.description: Definition of MPLS Label. The bits in network order (left-to-right) are, Label(20-bits):QOS(3-bits):Bottom-of-Stack(1-bit):TTL(8-bits) These constitute the 32-bit unsigned integer.

f3Pwe3IdlePatternProfileTable.name: f3Pwe3IdlePatternProfileTable
f3Pwe3IdlePatternProfileTable.description: A list of entries corresponding to the PWE3 Idle Pattern Profile entities.

f3Pwe3IdlePatternProfileEntry.name: f3Pwe3IdlePatternProfileEntry
f3Pwe3IdlePatternProfileEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a particular PWE3 Idle Pattern Profile Entity. These profiles are used by PWE3 SAToP entities.

f3Pwe3IdlePatternProfileIndex.name: f3Pwe3IdlePatternProfileIndex
f3Pwe3IdlePatternProfileIndex.description: Unique index value associated with the PWE3 Idle Pattern Profile.

f3Pwe3IdlePatternProfileByte.name: f3Pwe3IdlePatternProfileByte
f3Pwe3IdlePatternProfileByte.description: This object allows SNMP management entities to specify the Idle Pattern Profile information.

f3Pwe3ResyncProfileTable.name: f3Pwe3ResyncProfileTable
f3Pwe3ResyncProfileTable.description: A list of entries corresponding to the PWE3 Resync Profile entities.

f3Pwe3ResyncProfileEntry.name: f3Pwe3ResyncProfileEntry
f3Pwe3ResyncProfileEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a particular PWE3 Resync Profile Entity. These profiles are used by PWE3 SAToP entities.

f3Pwe3ResyncProfileIndex.name: f3Pwe3ResyncProfileIndex
f3Pwe3ResyncProfileIndex.description: Unique index value associated with the PWE3 Resync Profile.

f3Pwe3ResyncProfileIncreaseFactor.name: f3Pwe3ResyncProfileIncreaseFactor
f3Pwe3ResyncProfileIncreaseFactor.description: This object allows SNMP management entities to specify the PWE3 Resync Profile Increase Factor. This is used to define the fill rate of the leaky bucket algorithm associated with the Resync mechanism.

f3Pwe3ResyncProfileDecreaseFactor.name: f3Pwe3ResyncProfileDecreaseFactor
f3Pwe3ResyncProfileDecreaseFactor.description: This object allows SNMP management entities to specify the PWE3 Resync Profile Decrease Factor. This is used to define the leak rate for the leaky bucket algorithm associated with the Resync mechanism.

f3Pwe3ResyncProfileResyncThreshold.name: f3Pwe3ResyncProfileResyncThreshold
f3Pwe3ResyncProfileResyncThreshold.description: This object allows SNMP management entities to specify the PWE3 Resync Profile Resync Threshold. This is the threshold value at which point the pseudo-wire connection is deemed out of synchronization state.

f3Pwe3LoopbackProfileTable.name: f3Pwe3LoopbackProfileTable
f3Pwe3LoopbackProfileTable.description: A list of entries corresponding to the PWE3 Loopback Profile entities.

f3Pwe3LoopbackProfileEntry.name: f3Pwe3LoopbackProfileEntry
f3Pwe3LoopbackProfileEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a particular PWE3 Loopback Profile Entity. These profiles are used by PWE3 T1/E1 interfaces.

f3Pwe3LoopbackProfileIndex.name: f3Pwe3LoopbackProfileIndex
f3Pwe3LoopbackProfileIndex.description: Unique index value associated with the PWE3 Loopback Profile.

f3Pwe3LoopbackProfileLength.name: f3Pwe3LoopbackProfileLength
f3Pwe3LoopbackProfileLength.description: This object allows SNMP management entities to specify the PWE3 Loopback Length.

f3Pwe3LoopbackProfilePattern.name: f3Pwe3LoopbackProfilePattern
f3Pwe3LoopbackProfilePattern.description: This object allows SNMP management entities to specify the PWE3 Loopback Pattern.

f3Pwe3LoopbackProfileRepeatTime.name: f3Pwe3LoopbackProfileRepeatTime
f3Pwe3LoopbackProfileRepeatTime.description: This object allows SNMP management entities to specify the PWE3 Loopback Profile Repeat Time (Duration).

f3Pwe3LoopbackProfileClearLength.name: f3Pwe3LoopbackProfileClearLength
f3Pwe3LoopbackProfileClearLength.description: This object allows SNMP management entities to specify the Loopback PWE3 Clear Length.

f3Pwe3LoopbackProfileClearPattern.name: f3Pwe3LoopbackProfileClearPattern
f3Pwe3LoopbackProfileClearPattern.description: This object allows SNMP management entities to specify the PWE3 Loopback Clear Pattern.

f3Pwe3LossProfileTable.name: f3Pwe3LossProfileTable
f3Pwe3LossProfileTable.description: A list of entries corresponding to the PWE3 Loss Profile entities.

f3Pwe3LossProfileEntry.name: f3Pwe3LossProfileEntry
f3Pwe3LossProfileEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a particular PWE3 Loss Profile Entity. These profiles are used by PWE3 SAToP entities.

f3Pwe3LossProfileIndex.name: f3Pwe3LossProfileIndex
f3Pwe3LossProfileIndex.description: Unique index value associated with the PWE3 Loss Profile.

f3Pwe3LossProfileLossStateEnterTime.name: f3Pwe3LossProfileLossStateEnterTime
f3Pwe3LossProfileLossStateEnterTime.description: This object allows SNMP management entities to specify the holdoff time that will be applied prior to the SAToP instance entering a Loss State.

f3Pwe3LossProfileLossStateExitTime.name: f3Pwe3LossProfileLossStateExitTime
f3Pwe3LossProfileLossStateExitTime.description: This object allows SNMP management entities to specify the holdon time that will be applied when the conditon causing the loss state clears.

f3Pwe3AisStabilizationProfileTable.name: f3Pwe3AisStabilizationProfileTable
f3Pwe3AisStabilizationProfileTable.description: A list of entries corresponding to the PWE3 AisStabilization Profile entities.

f3Pwe3AisStabilizationProfileEntry.name: f3Pwe3AisStabilizationProfileEntry
f3Pwe3AisStabilizationProfileEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a particular PWE3 AisStabilization Profile Entity. These profiles are used by PWE3 SAToP entities.

f3Pwe3AisStabilizationProfileIndex.name: f3Pwe3AisStabilizationProfileIndex
f3Pwe3AisStabilizationProfileIndex.description: Unique index value associated with the PWE3 AIS Stabilization Profile.

f3Pwe3AisStabilizationProfileEnterTime.name: f3Pwe3AisStabilizationProfileEnterTime
f3Pwe3AisStabilizationProfileEnterTime.description: This object allows SNMP management entities to specify the time (in hundreds of milliseconds) that will be applied on a LOS event, before the SAToP instance transmits all 1s pattern downstream (AIS). Range 0 to 3 seconds in 100 millisecond increments.

f3Pwe3AisStabilizationProfileExitTime.name: f3Pwe3AisStabilizationProfileExitTime
f3Pwe3AisStabilizationProfileExitTime.description: This object allows SNMP management entities to specify the holdon time that will be applied when leaving the AIS Stabilization period. Range 0 to 3 seconds in 100 milliseconds increments (e.g. parameter range is 0 to 30).

f3Pwe3SatopTable.name: f3Pwe3SatopTable
f3Pwe3SatopTable.description: A list of entries corresponding to the PWE3 SAToP entities.

f3Pwe3SatopEntry.name: f3Pwe3SatopEntry
f3Pwe3SatopEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a particular PWE3 SAToP Entity.

f3Pwe3SatopIndex.name: f3Pwe3SatopIndex
f3Pwe3SatopIndex.description: Unique index value associated with the SAToP Entity.

f3Pwe3SatopAlias.name: f3Pwe3SatopAlias
f3Pwe3SatopAlias.description: This object allows SNMP management entities to provide an alias to the PWE3 SAToP entity.

f3Pwe3SatopAdminState.name: f3Pwe3SatopAdminState
f3Pwe3SatopAdminState.description: This object represents the Administrative State of the PWE3 SAToP entity.

f3Pwe3SatopOperationalState.name: f3Pwe3SatopOperationalState
f3Pwe3SatopOperationalState.description: This object represents the Operational State of the PWE3 SAToP entity.

f3Pwe3SatopSecondaryState.name: f3Pwe3SatopSecondaryState
f3Pwe3SatopSecondaryState.description: This object represents the Secondary State of the PWE3 SAToP entity.

f3Pwe3SatopTDMEntity.name: f3Pwe3SatopTDMEntity
f3Pwe3SatopTDMEntity.description: This object allows specification of the T1/E1 entity associated with the SAToP. This is only used at SATop creation time. Result of get operation on this object will result with zeroDotZero since one Satop could have more then one associated TDM entity. Subsequently, the associated TDM entities are managed via f3Pwe3SatopTDMEntityTable.

f3Pwe3SatopDiscoveryType.name: f3Pwe3SatopDiscoveryType
f3Pwe3SatopDiscoveryType.description: This object allows ability to statically/dynamically determine the MAC address of the remote IP Address associated with the SAToP. In the case of static discovery type, f3Pwe3SatopRemoteMacAddress must be explicitly specified. In the case of dynamic discovery, the system will use ARP mechanism to obtain the remote Layer 2 MAC address.

f3Pwe3SatopRemoteIpAddress.name: f3Pwe3SatopRemoteIpAddress
f3Pwe3SatopRemoteIpAddress.description: This object allows ability to specify the remote IP Address. This is used in the PWE payload.

f3Pwe3SatopRemoteMacAddress.name: f3Pwe3SatopRemoteMacAddress
f3Pwe3SatopRemoteMacAddress.description: This object allows ability to specify the remote Layer 2 MAC Address. This must be specified in case of f3Pwe3SatopDiscoveryType as static. This is derived dynamically (via ARP) if f3Pwe3SatopDiscoveryType is dynamic, i.e. it does not have to be specified.

f3Pwe3SatopEncapsulationType.name: f3Pwe3SatopEncapsulationType
f3Pwe3SatopEncapsulationType.description: This object allows ability to specify the encapsulation type of the SATop. It can be encapsulated with VLAN and single MPLS label(vlan-one-mpls-label), VLAN and two MPLS labels (vlan-two-mpls-label), untagged and two MPLS labels (novlan-two-mpls-label) .

f3Pwe3SatopRTPEnabled.name: f3Pwe3SatopRTPEnabled
f3Pwe3SatopRTPEnabled.description: This object enables/disables RTP header for this SATop instance.

f3Pwe3SatopRTPUpdateFrequency.name: f3Pwe3SatopRTPUpdateFrequency
f3Pwe3SatopRTPUpdateFrequency.description: When f3Pwe3SatopRTPEnabled is true, this object allows specification of the RTP clock update frequency.

f3Pwe3SatopControlWordEnabled.name: f3Pwe3SatopControlWordEnabled
f3Pwe3SatopControlWordEnabled.description: This object is used for 3rd party interoperability, since earlier versions of PWE do not support control-word.

f3Pwe3SatopJitterBufferSize.name: f3Pwe3SatopJitterBufferSize
f3Pwe3SatopJitterBufferSize.description: This object allows definition of size of the jitter buffer in microseconds for this SATop instance.

f3Pwe3SatopPayloadSize.name: f3Pwe3SatopPayloadSize
f3Pwe3SatopPayloadSize.description: This object allows specification of the SATop payload size.

f3Pwe3SatopVlanId.name: f3Pwe3SatopVlanId
f3Pwe3SatopVlanId.description: This object allows specification of the SATop VLAN Id. Applicable for vlan based encapsulation types.

f3Pwe3SatopVlanPriority.name: f3Pwe3SatopVlanPriority
f3Pwe3SatopVlanPriority.description: This object allows specification of the SATop VLAN Priority. Applicable for vlan based encapsulation types.

f3Pwe3SatopRxMplsLabel1.name: f3Pwe3SatopRxMplsLabel1
f3Pwe3SatopRxMplsLabel1.description: This object allows specification of the expected receive MPLS Label. Applicable for single MPLS label encapsulation type.

f3Pwe3SatopRxMplsLabel2.name: f3Pwe3SatopRxMplsLabel2
f3Pwe3SatopRxMplsLabel2.description: This object allows specification of the expected receive MPLS Label. Applicable for dual MPLS label encapsulation types.

f3Pwe3SatopTxMplsLabel1.name: f3Pwe3SatopTxMplsLabel1
f3Pwe3SatopTxMplsLabel1.description: This object allows specification of the transmitted MPLS Label, used for multiplexing. Applicable for single MPLS label encapsulation type.

f3Pwe3SatopTxMplsLabel2.name: f3Pwe3SatopTxMplsLabel2
f3Pwe3SatopTxMplsLabel2.description: This object allows specification of the transmitted MPLS Label, used for multiplexing. Applicable for dual MPLS label encapsulation type.

f3Pwe3SatopAisStabilizationProfile.name: f3Pwe3SatopAisStabilizationProfile
f3Pwe3SatopAisStabilizationProfile.description: This object allows specification of the AIS stabilization Profile object. If no profile is associated, this value should be 0.0.

f3Pwe3SatopResyncProfile.name: f3Pwe3SatopResyncProfile
f3Pwe3SatopResyncProfile.description: This object allows specification of the Resync Profile object. If no profile is associated, this value should be 0.0.

f3Pwe3SatopLossProfile.name: f3Pwe3SatopLossProfile
f3Pwe3SatopLossProfile.description: This object allows specification of the Loss Profile object. If no profile is associated, this value should be 0.0.

f3Pwe3SatopTransportMode.name: f3Pwe3SatopTransportMode
f3Pwe3SatopTransportMode.description: This object allows specification of the SATop transport mode.

f3Pwe3SatopStorageType.name: f3Pwe3SatopStorageType
f3Pwe3SatopStorageType.description: The type of storage configured for this entry.

f3Pwe3SatopRowStatus.name: f3Pwe3SatopRowStatus
f3Pwe3SatopRowStatus.description: The status of this row. An entry MUST NOT exist in the active state unless all objects in the entry have an appropriate value, as described in the description clause for each writable object. The values of f3Pwe3SatopRowStatus supported are createAndGo(4) and destroy(6). All mandatory attributes must be specified in a single SNMP SET request with f3Pwe3SatopRowStatus value as createAndGo(4). Upon successful row creation, this object has a value of active(1). The f3Pwe3SatopRowStatus object may be modified if the associated instance of this object is equal to active(1).

f3Pwe3SatopTDMEntitiesTable.name: f3Pwe3SatopTDMEntitiesTable
f3Pwe3SatopTDMEntitiesTable.description: A list of entries corresponding to the PWE3 SATop TDM entities .

f3Pwe3SatopTDMEntitiesEntry.name: f3Pwe3SatopTDMEntitiesEntry
f3Pwe3SatopTDMEntitiesEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a particular PWE3 SATop TDM entity.

f3Pwe3SatopTDMEntityIndex.name: f3Pwe3SatopTDMEntityIndex
f3Pwe3SatopTDMEntityIndex.description: Unique index value associated with the PWE3 SATOP TDM Entity.

f3Pwe3SatopTDMEntityObject.name: f3Pwe3SatopTDMEntityObject
f3Pwe3SatopTDMEntityObject.description: This object points to the PWE3 SATOP TDM Entity. This is OID of the actual T1/E1 interface.

f3Pwe3SatopTDMEntityStorageType.name: f3Pwe3SatopTDMEntityStorageType
f3Pwe3SatopTDMEntityStorageType.description: The type of storage configured for this entry.

f3Pwe3SatopTDMEntityRowStatus.name: f3Pwe3SatopTDMEntityRowStatus
f3Pwe3SatopTDMEntityRowStatus.description: The status of this row. An entry MUST NOT exist in the active state unless all objects in the entry have an appropriate value, as described in the description clause for each writable object. The values of f3Pwe3SatopTDMEntityRowStatus supported are createAndGo(4) and destroy(6). All mandatory attributes must be specified in a single SNMP SET request with f3Pwe3SatopTDMEntityRowStatus value as createAndGo(4). Upon successful row creation, this object has a value of active(1). The f3Pwe3SatopTDMEntityRowStatus object may be modified if the associated instance of this object is equal to active(1).
